==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tellureted
<hw>Tel"lu*ret`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Combined or impregnated with tellurium; tellurized.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>telluretted</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[Obsoles.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tellureted hydrogen</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>hydrogen telluride, <chform>H2Te</chform>, a gaseous substance
analogous to hydrogen sulphide; -- called also <altname>tellurhydric
acid</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tellurhydric</ent>⟦br⟧
